<span id="xi.i-p13"></span>There are two remarkable resemblances between
Jeremiah and Moses. They both made an excuse for declining the office to
which God called them, and made a similar excuse. The other resemblance
is what *Lightfoot* has noticed, that Moses was a teacher of the people
for *forty years* before they entered the land of Canaan, and that
Jeremiah was their teacher for *forty years* before they were banished
from it and driven into exile. — *Ed*.

