id="xi.i-p16.1"></span>

<span id="xi.i-p17"></span> The reasons alleged against Jeremiah being
the son of the high priest are by no means conclusive: indeed, all the
circumstances being considered, the probability is in favor of that
supposition. The family of the high priest resided no doubt at Anathoth;
what is said in <span id="xi.i-p17.1"></span>[1Ki
2:26](../../../bib/kjv/kg1002.htm#026.md)<span id="xi.i-p17.1"></span>,
respecting Abiathar, is a proof of this. That the high priest resided at
